<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="131" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
Male. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Coloration</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Antennae with scape and pedicel yellowish-brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Amydetes alexi sp. nov., head A dorsal B ventral C frontal D lateral E posterior F occipital; antennae G dorsal. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-F); 2 mm (G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720422" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">14G</figureCitation>
), flagellum dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Amydetes alexi sp. nov., head A dorsal B ventral C frontal D lateral E posterior F occipital; antennae G dorsal. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-F); 2 mm (G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720422" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">14G</figureCitation>
); pronotal disc dark brown with margins yellowish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Amydetes alexi sp. nov., pronotum A dorsal B ventral C lateral D posterior. Scale bar: 1 mm (A-D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720423" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">15A, B</figureCitation>
); elytra dark brown with outer margin yellow (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Amydetes alexi sp. nov., male habitus A ventral B lateral C dorsal. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720421" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">13A-C</figureCitation>
); posterolateral margin of thorax yellowish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Amydetes alexi sp. nov., male habitus A ventral B lateral C dorsal. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720421" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">13A</figureCitation>
); legs yellowish brown darkened to dark brown toward apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Amydetes alexi sp. nov., male habitus A ventral B lateral C dorsal. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720421" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">13A</figureCitation>
); sides of sternites II-V translucent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Amydetes alexi sp. nov., male habitus A ventral B lateral C dorsal. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720421" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">13A</figureCitation>
); sternite VIII translucent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Amydetes alexi sp. nov., aedeagus A dorsal B lateral C ventral; sternum IX D ventral. sternite VIII E ventral; pygidium F dorsal. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A-D); 1 mm (E-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720424" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">16E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Antennae flabellate with 33-37 antennomeres (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Amydetes alexi sp. nov., head A dorsal B ventral C frontal D lateral E posterior F occipital; antennae G dorsal. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-F); 2 mm (G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720422" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">14G</figureCitation>
); antennomere III 1/2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than scape, with flabellum 3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than antennomere III. Fronto-clypeus as wide as 1/2 distance between antennifers process (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Amydetes alexi sp. nov., head A dorsal B ventral C frontal D lateral E posterior F occipital; antennae G dorsal. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-F); 2 mm (G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720422" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">14C</figureCitation>
). Maxillary and labial apical palpomere subequal in length (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Amydetes alexi sp. nov., head A dorsal B ventral C frontal D lateral E posterior F occipital; antennae G dorsal. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-F); 2 mm (G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1114.77692.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720422" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">14A-E</figureCitation>
); maxillary palpomere I, II and IV 2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
