<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Campello, Vaz, Mermudes &amp; Silveira" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Amydetes alexi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Amydetes alexi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. bellorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="bellorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. bellorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. marolae" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="marolae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. marolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. in the length of maxillary palpomere IV, which is at least 6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than III in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. marolae" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="marolae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. marolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. bellorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="bellorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. bellorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but only 3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than III in three species: 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. itatiaia" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="itatiaia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. itatiaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. alexi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="alexi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. alexi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Campello, Vaz, Mermudes &amp; Silveira" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Amydetes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Amydetes alexi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">Amydetes alexi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. itatiaia" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="itatiaia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. itatiaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the length of flabellum of antennomere III (3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than pedicel in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. alexi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="alexi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. alexi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., but equal in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. itatiaia" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="itatiaia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. itatiaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The new species shares the following traits with 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: pronotum with posterolateral angles pointed but weakly developed; flabellum of antennomere III 3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than pedicel; and phallobase asymmetrical. Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. alexi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="alexi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. alexi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having antennae with 33-37 antennomeres (37-44 in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and lantern of sternite VI up to 1/2 sternite length (3/5 in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The distribution of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. alexi" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" rank="species" species="alexi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="131">A. alexi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is apparently restricted to Pedra Branca massif, as it has not been found nearby by our team (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2020.1749323" author="Silveira, LFL" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="131" pagination="275 - 308" refId="B31" refString="Silveira, LFL, Khattar, G, Vaz, S, Wilson, VA, Souto, PM, Mermudes, JRM, Monteiro, RF, 2020. Natural history of the fireflies of the Serra dos Orgaos mountain range (Brazil: Rio de Janeiro)-one of the 'hottest' firefly spots on Earth, with a key to genera (Coleoptera: Lampyridae). Journal of Natural History 54 (5-6): 275 - 308, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2020.1749323" title="Natural history of the fireflies of the Serra dos Orgaos mountain range (Brazil: Rio de Janeiro) - one of the ' hottest' firefly spots on Earth, with a key to genera (Coleoptera: Lampyridae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2020.1749323" volume="54" year="2020">Silveira et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
